  <summary date="2007-09-13T18:39:30Z" status="Introduced in House">Children's Health Protection Act of 2007 - Amends the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974 (ERISA), the Public Health Service Act, and the Internal Revenue Code to prohibit a group health plan from imposing any preexisting condition exclusion for individuals who have not attained 19 years of age.

Applies such requirement to coverage offered in the individual market.</summary>
